@node features "Features"

                               Features

-Simple installation: just run the game and play!

-Pyramid is a "Workbench" game, so it's meant to be played on the
 Workbench screen. The game window can be resized up to a maximum of
 640 x 400 pixels, and the game is redisplayed according to the new
 window size. If the window is too small, it will automatically be
 resized to an adequate displayable size.

-You can play the game with the mouse or with the cursor keys of the
 keyboard.

-As the game uses as little of the computer's ressources as possible,
 you can run other applications, games, etc. at the same time.

-Pyramid works on all Amigas with Workbench 1.3 or higher.

@endnode

@node histo "History"

                               Versions History

  What follows are the various updates that were done since the first version
of this game.

1.0:  -First public release.

1.01: -Now you can click in the general direction where you want to go, not
       just the space next to your position... that's not much (especially
       with a 5 by 5 display) but it's better than before (personally, I use
       the cursor keys of the keyboard to move in the pyramid)...
      -Bugfix: the game crashed on an Amiga using Workbench 1.3...
      -The pyramid 'construction' routine has been revised.

1.02: -Some minor changes were made to the program code.

1.03: -Bugfix: When the 'About' window was displayed and it overlapped
       the game board, the player could click on the positions 'through'
       the About window.
      -Various changes have been made to the program code: the routine to
       generate the main game window has been revised, the routine that
       displays the game board has been enhanced, unneeded program code
       was removed, etc.

1.1: Various changes have been made to the program code:
      -The player movement routine has been revised.
      -The routine that checks if the game window is too small has been
       revised.
      -Now the game window can be resized up to a 640 by 400 pixel size.
      -Some unneeded code has been removed.
      -Some minor changes have been made.

1.2: -Now, when the Workbench has 8 colours or more, a routine checks if
      the yellow colour is available on the Workbench palette, if it is,
      the topmost part of the pyramid will be coloured in yellow.
     -The buttons have been redrawn.
     -The 'progress bar' routine has been revised.
     -Some other portions of the program code has been revised.

@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Pyramid" where you want 
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  At the start of a game, your location is at the lower left of the
pyramid; your position is indicated by a white human figure and is always
located in the center of the display. To move, click on any space or tile
in the general direction you want to go, if you are in front or on top of
a ladder, click on a space above or below your position to go in the
desired direction. If the move is possible, the display will be updated
at the new position. Note that you can also use the cursor keys to move
in the pyramid.

  The Pharaoh's tomb is located at the top of the pyramid. If you get
there, the game ends and displays how many moves it took to get there,
then the game creates a new pyramid to explore...

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub} button
(or with the Right-Amiga + "N" key combination).

  Have fun!

@endnode

